Package eu.unite.challenge.algorithms

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractProblemSolver
    The Solver class provides a base class for various algorithms implementing the solution to the given problem.
    BranchAndBoundAlgoImpl
    BranchAndBoundAlgoImpl is similar to BruteForceAlgoImpl, but it uses heuristics so that only plausible solutions in the solution space are traversed.
    BranchAndBoundAlgoImpl.Node
    A class representing a node in the solution tree
    BranchAndBoundAlgoImplTest  
    BruteForceAlgoImpl
    This class is the simplest extension of AbstractProblemSolver, and solves the problem by exhaustively searching the solution space.
    BruteForceAlgoImplTest  
    DynamicProgrammingAlgoImpl
    is a pseudo-polynomial algorithm: It is polynomial time in the value W, which denotes the number of possible weights (if the weights are fractional, we can multiply them by a common factor so that they are all integers.) It works by trading space for time: A large table is used to memoize state for subproblems.
    DynamicProgrammingAlgoImplTest  
    GreedyApproximationAlgoImpl
    This class uses the greedy approach explained previously, with one twist: It greedily picks a subset of items until the weight constraint allows no more.
    GreedyApproximationAlgoImplTest  
    ItemComparators
    Keeps comparators used by various algorithms.
